# ws-ex Engineering (Cursor)

## Stack

- `chat-service/`: Go · Gin · NATS JetStream · Postgres · LiveKit tokens · JWT
- `front-chat/`: SvelteKit 5 · Svelte 5 runes · Tailwind 4 · shadcn-svelte · pnpm
- Compose: nats · postgres · livekit · ws-server · frontend (nginx)

## Architecture

- Backend layers: `controller` → `service` → `model`/`dto`; routes in `router/`; validation in `validate/`
- Frontend: `$lib/api/*` (HTTP/WS) → `$lib/chat/controller/*` → `$lib/chat/components/*`
- Messages: WS frames, `id`+`seq`, private direct / group NATS fan-out, JetStream history (~180d)
- Pagination: `before_seq`/`before_ts` older; `since_seq` newer; client `has_more`
- Group roles: owner > admin > member

## Commands

```bash
docker compose up -d --build
cd chat-service && go run ./cmd/server && go test ./...
cd front-chat && pnpm install && pnpm dev
cd front-chat && pnpm check && pnpm lint && pnpm test
```

Use **pnpm** only in `front-chat`.

## Rules of change

1. Minimal diffs; no drive-by refactors
2. Keep DTO ↔ `types.ts` ↔ API client in sync
3. Svelte 5: `$state` / `$derived` / `$props` / `$effect` only
4. UI Chinese; toasts via `$lib/ui/notify.svelte.ts` (no `window.alert`)
5. Do not commit secrets; do not force-push unless asked
6. After UI/TS changes run `pnpm check`; after Go logic run tests/build

## Feature map (where to edit)

